        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><b>Preventing Crimes Against Veterans Act of 2021</b></p> <p>This bill establishes a new criminal offense for knowingly executing, or attempting to execute, a scheme to defraud an individual of veterans' benefits, or in connection with obtaining veteran's benefits for an individual. A violator is subject to criminal penalties&#8212;a fine, a prison term of up to five years, or both.</p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
